2 WHEREAS, the federal government has ceased to operate under
3 a proper interpretation of the Constitution of the United
4 States; and
5
6 WHEREAS, it is the solemn duty of the states to protect the
7 liberty of the people, particularly for future generations,
8 by proposing amendments to the Constitution of the United
9 States through a convention of the states under Article V of
10 the United States Constitution for the purpose of restraining
11 these and related abuses of power.
12
13 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE MEMBERS OF THE
14 LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF WYOMING:
15
16 Section 1. That the Legislature of the State of Wyoming
17 hereby applies to Congress, under the provisions of Article
18 V of the Constitution of the United States, for the calling
19 of a convention of the several states limited to proposing
20 amendments to the Constitution of the United States that
21 impose fiscal restraints on the federal government, limit the
22 power and jurisdiction of the federal government and limit
