1 this application from two-thirds (2/3) of the legislatures of
2 the several states;
3
4 (iii) Congress does not have the power or
5 authority to determine any rules for the governing of an
6 amendment convention of the several states called pursuant to
7 Article V of the United States Constitution. Congress does
8 not have the power to set the number of delegates to be sent
9 by any state to a convention nor does it have the power to
10 name delegates to a convention. The power to name delegates
11 remains exclusively within the authority of the legislatures
12 of the several states;
13
14 (iv) By definition, a convention of the states to
15 propose amendments to the United States Constitution means
16 that states shall vote on the basis of one (1) state, one (1)
17 vote;
18
19 (v) A convention of the several states to propose
20 amendments to the Constitution convened pursuant to this
21 application shall be limited to consideration of the topics
22 specified in this joint resolution and no other. This
23 application is made with the express understanding that an
