1 amendment that in any way seeks to amend, modify or repeal
2 any provision of the Bill of Rights shall not be authorized
3 for consideration in any manner;
4
5 (vi) Pursuant to Article V of the United States
6 Constitution, Congress may determine whether proposed
7 amendments shall be ratified by the legislatures of the
8 several states or by special state ratification conventions.
9 The Legislature of the State of Wyoming recommends that
10 Congress select ratification by the legislatures of the
11 several states; and
12
13 (vii) The Legislature of the State of Wyoming may
14 provide further instructions to its delegates and may recall
15 its delegates at any time for a breach of a duty or a violation
16 of the instructions provided to the delegates.
17
18 Section 3. That this application constitutes a
19 continuing application in accordance with Article V of the
20 Constitution of the United States until the legislatures of
21 at least two-thirds (2/3) of the several states have made
22 applications on the same subject.
